                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This archaic inscription belongs to the 10th year of the same <hi rend="bold">Kampavarman</hi> whose name occurred in No. <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv03p0i0005">5</ref> above, and records that <hi rend="bold">Śaḍaiyaṉ</hi>, who was also mentioned in No. <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv03p0i0005">5</ref>, made over 400 <hi rend="italic">kāḍi</hi> of paddy to the villagers of <hi rend="bold">Uṭakal</hi>, who pledged themselves to feed two Brāhmaṇas daily from the interest, which amounted to 100 <hi rend="italic">kāḍi</hi> of paddy per year.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
